                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "As a standard action, a marid can emit a bolt of heat-sapping water in a 60-foot line. The marid can choose whether or not this line of water deals damage. Regardless, the line ends the burning condition on any creature it hits and puts out fires in its area. If a fire is magical, it goes out only if its creator is of a CR or level equal to or lower than the marid\u2019s CR.<br/>In addition, the marid can cause the bolt to be continuous. Doing so has no additional effect on targets already within the line, but anything that moves across the line is attacked using the original attack roll and damage. A target the line hits but doesn\u2019t damage blocks the line as normal. If an existing blockage is removed, the line extends out to its maximum range unless blocked anew, and it can damage creatures and objects it failed to reach previously. The marid can\u2019t damage a target more than once per round with this continuous line. If the marid moves from where the line was initiated, the line ends immediately.",
                "name": "Water Bolt",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            },
